==English==

===Etymology===
From {{NL.}} {{term|ephemerus}} < {{etyl|grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ἐφήμερος|tr=ephēmeros}}, the more common form of {{term|ἐφημέριος|tr=ephemerios|sc=polytonic||of, for, or during the day, living or lasting but for a day, short-lived, temporary}} < {{term|έπί|tr=epi|sc=polytonic||on}} + {{term|ήμέρα|tr=emera|sc=polytonic||day}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɛˈfɛmərəl/|/əˈfɛmərəl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-ephemeral.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Lasting for a [[short]] period of [[time]].
# {{biology}} Existing for only [[one]] [[day]], as with some [[flower]]s, [[insect]]s, and [[disease]]s.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|lasting for a short period of time}}: [[temporary]], [[transitory]], [[fleeting]], [[evanescent]], [[momentary]], [[short-lived]], [[short]], [[volatile]]
* See also [[Wikisaurus:ephemeral]]

====Antonyms====
* {{sense|lasting for a long period of time}}: [[permanent]], [[eternal]], [[everlasting]], [[timeless]].

